**PROJECT PROPOSAL**

Internal Ship-Package Tracking & Logistics Management System

*Version 2.0*

# 1. Executive Summary

The company proposes the development of an internal Ship-Package Tracking & Logistics Management System to manage the full operational lifecycle of customer packages transported between international warehouses (Lebanon and Gabon) using shared shipment containers.

The system will be used exclusively by company employees and will centralize logistics operations currently handled through manual processes, spreadsheets, and messaging applications. The solution will provide full traceability, pricing control, documentation compliance, and operational efficiency across all warehouses and shipment cycles.

# 2. Project Objectives

The primary objectives of this project are to:

1. Track customer packages from origin warehouse to destination warehouse

1. Consolidate packages from multiple customers into shared shipment containers

1. Enforce structured package classification, documentation, and pricing rules

1. Ensure accurate photo evidence at every warehouse stage with customer identification

1. Automate container sequencing and package allocation

1. Enforce container capacity control (weight & m²) with configurable warnings

1. Generate invoices, packing lists, and Excel reports per customer

1. Support bilingual product catalog (Arabic/English) with stored pricing

1. Track vessel movement and provide estimated arrival dates

1. Handle additional fees (port charges, internal transport)

1. Improve coordination between warehouses in different countries

1. Reduce operational risk, errors, and disputes

1. Enable scalable, repeatable shipment operations year over year

