# 5. Operational Workflow

## 5.1 Customer Registration & Initial Booking

1. Customer calls to book shipment

1. Staff enters preliminary (approximate) information into the system

1. System automatically assigns a permanent unique customer ID

1. Customer name and phone number are recorded

1. Staff can print or share price list with customer manually

## 5.2 Goods Receipt at Origin Warehouse

1. When goods arrive at the warehouse, staff enters accurate/final information

1. Photos of the goods are taken and attached to the record

1. Customer name is automatically overlaid on photos for identification

1. Goods type is selected from bilingual catalog (Arabic name auto-translates to English)

1. System suggests default pricing based on goods type (with stored discounted prices if applicable)

1. Weight and m² measurements are recorded

1. Compliance documents are auto-generated based on goods type

1. Documents are printed for customer signature (responsibility declaration, drug-free certification)

1. Signed documents are scanned/photographed and uploaded to the system

## 5.3 Container Assignment & Loading

1. Confirmed packages are assigned to the oldest Pending container

1. Draft packages are assigned to the next available Pending container

1. System continuously tracks total weight and m² against container limits

1. Visual warnings displayed when approaching capacity threshold (configurable: 80-90%)

1. Container status changes to 'Nearly Full' when threshold is reached

1. Assignment prevented if it would exceed container limits

1. All assignments and reassignments are logged

## 5.4 Pre-Shipment Documentation

Once goods are ready for loading, the system generates per customer:

-   Photo album with all goods photos (each photo labeled with customer name)

-   Signed compliance documents

-   Goods type and classification

-   Shipping price breakdown

-   Agreement document ready for customer

## 5.5 Vessel Tracking & Updates

-   Staff enters vessel name and tracking information

-   Estimated departure and arrival dates are recorded

-   Staff can add weekly updates on vessel location/status

-   Updates are logged with timestamps

-   Staff can manually notify customers of updates via their preferred channel

## 5.6 Document Generation

The system generates:

-   Packing List - complete inventory of container contents

-   Commercial Invoice - with reduced/declared prices for customs (entered once per product, then stored for future use)

-   Customer Invoice - actual shipping charges with any additional fees

## 5.7 Destination Warehouse Operations (Gabon)

1. Staff has full access to shipment data, customer information, and all photos

1. Photos are labeled with customer names for easy identification during unloading

1. Staff can view signed documents and goods classifications

1. Upon customer pickup, delivery confirmation photo is taken

1. Photo of signed receipt is uploaded to the system

1. Package marked as delivered

## 5.8 Container Closure

-   Container closed when all packages are delivered

-   Complete file archived with all details, photos, documents, and receipts

-   Financial records locked after approval

