-   Auto-generated reference: YYYY-XX (e.g., 2026-01, 2026-02)

-   Counter resets annually

# 7. ShipmentContainer Sequencing & Capacity Control

## 7.1 Container Capacity Limits

Each ShipmentContainer must define:

-   Maximum Weight (kg)

-   Maximum Area (m²)

The system must:

-   Continuously calculate total assigned weight and m²

-   Display running totals to operators

-   Prevent assignments that exceed limits

## 7.2 Capacity Warning Thresholds

-   Visual and system warnings when weight or m² reaches configurable threshold (default: 80-90%)

-   Container status automatically changes to 'Nearly Full' when threshold is reached

-   Alerts displayed on dashboard for logistics management

**Business Value:** Prevents overloading and allows proactive shipment planning.

## 7.3 Container Status Lifecycle

|             |                                         |
|-------------|-----------------------------------------|
| **Status**  | **Description**                         |
| Draft       | Initial creation, not yet active        |
| Pending     | Open for package assignment             |
| Nearly Full | Approaching capacity threshold          |
| Loaded      | All packages loaded, ready for shipment |
| Shipped     | In transit                              |
| Arrived     | Arrived at destination warehouse        |
| Completed   | All packages delivered                  |
| Closed      | Archived with all documentation         |

## 7.4 Minimum Active Containers Rule

-   At least two (2) Pending ShipmentContainers must always exist

-   System alerts when minimum threshold is not met

-   New containers can be quickly created from the interface

